# ============================================================
# GIT MASTER - Team Deployment Configuration
# ============================================================
# This is a pre-configured .env for team deployment
# Users should add their personal GITHUB_TOKEN before using

# --- GITHUB AUTHENTICATION ---
# IMPORTANT: Each user must add their own token here!
GITHUB_TOKEN=""                    # ← ADD YOUR PERSONAL TOKEN HERE
GITHUB_USERNAME=""                 # ← ADD YOUR GITHUB USERNAME HERE

# --- SHARED PATH CONFIGURATION ---
# These paths are configured for our team's setup
# Adjust if your local setup differs

# QNAP Setup (default)
PATH_ROOT="/share/Web"

# macOS Setup (uncomment if using Mac)
# PATH_ROOT="$HOME/Projects"

# Linux Setup (uncomment if using Linux)
# PATH_ROOT="$HOME/workspace"

# Automatically derived paths (usually no changes needed)
# PATH_PROD="${PATH_ROOT}"
# PATH_DEV="${PATH_ROOT}/DEV"
# PATH_TEST="${PATH_ROOT}/TEST"

# --- QNAP PERSISTENCE ---
# For QNAP users: these paths ensure persistence across reboots
# PERSISTENT_SCRIPT_PATH="${PATH_DEV}/scripts/git-master.sh"
# PERSISTENT_ENV="${PATH_DEV}/scripts/.env"

# --- OPTIONAL TEAM SETTINGS ---
# DEFAULT_BRANCH="main"
# AUTO_PRUNE=true

# ============================================================
# INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env if not already done
# 2. Add your GITHUB_TOKEN and GITHUB_USERNAME above
# 3. Adjust PATH_ROOT if your setup differs
# 4. Run: ./install.sh
# 5. The installer will use this pre-configured file
#
# How to get a GitHub token:
# - Go to: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# - Generate new token (classic)
# - Select scopes: repo, workflow, delete_repo
# - Copy token and paste above
#
# ============================================================
